<p>I'm using Excel 2013 on Windows 7.</p>  <p>I did some Excel data checking using basic IF and some operators. And I encountered an issue that give me inconsistency in the result. I'm checking is:  </p>  <pre><code>1.24 = 66.64 - 65.4 </code></pre>  <p>Below is the formula I used and the result should be mathematically EQUAL, but it gives me NOT EQUAL:</p>  <pre><code>=IF(1.24 = 66.64 - 65.4, "EQUAL", "NOT EQUAL")     ;Result: NOT EQUAL </code></pre>  <p>I tried to modify the data slightly to:</p>  <pre><code>=IF(1.24 = 56.64 - 55.4, "EQUAL", "NOT EQUAL")     ;Result: EQUAL </code></pre>  <p>and I'm surprised that it return the correct result.</p>  <p>Is this a bug, and if so, is there any workaround I can use for similar checking?</p>